244
00:29:58,546 --> 00:30:00,548
THE FURNITURE.

245
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:03,551
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
HOW'D IT--

246
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:07,555
I BROUGHT IT BACK
AFTER THE CRASH.

247
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:10,058
HUH?
AND I WAS BLINDED.

248
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,060
BLINDED?

249
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:14,062
AND CARL WAS KILLED.

250
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:16,064
KILLED?

251
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:19,651
TWO YEARS AGO.

252
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,069
[ Screaming ]

253
00:30:29,694 --> 00:30:32,697
I'M SORRY. BAD DREAM.

254
00:30:32,697 --> 00:30:34,833
[ Horn Honking ]

255
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:38,837
- LOOK OUT!
-[ Tires Screeching ]

256
00:30:41,756 --> 00:30:44,209
[ Screaming ]

257
00:30:51,799 --> 00:30:53,601
[ Loud Crashing ]

258
00:31:01,943 --> 00:31:04,529
SO THAT IS WHY
YOU WERE IN A HURRY?

259
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:15,290
TO LEAVE YOUR WIFE
AND CHILDREN?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

260
00:31:17,909 --> 00:31:21,212
HOW DO YOU--
WHO ARE YOU?

261
00:31:25,083 --> 00:31:26,834
I ASSURE YOU,
 I HAVE A PURPOSE.

262
00:31:29,137 --> 00:31:32,140
WHAT SORT OF GAME
ARE YOU PLAYING?
GAME?

263
00:31:32,140 --> 00:31:34,425
YOU'RE TRYING TO
FRIGHTEN US IN SOME WAY.

264
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:37,512
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

265
00:31:39,931 --> 00:31:41,933
TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

266
00:31:41,933 --> 00:31:44,769
SOMETHING IN YOUR OWN MIND.

267
00:31:44,769 --> 00:31:47,655
SOMETHING YOU ARE CAPABLE
OF DOING.

268
00:31:47,655 --> 00:31:49,857
I DON'T WANNA KNOW.

269
00:31:49,857 --> 00:31:52,160
OH, BUT YOU MUST KNOW.

270
00:31:54,162 --> 00:31:56,164
YOU MUST.

271
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:03,788
[ Children Chattering,
  Laughing ]

272
00:32:26,060 --> 00:32:29,981
[ Chattering, Laughter
  Continue ]

273
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,654
THANK YOU.

274
00:32:37,155 --> 00:32:39,657
WE KNEW IT WAS YOU.
YOU KNEW IT WAS ME?

275
00:32:39,657 --> 00:32:42,160
DEAR OLD PUNCH THOUGH,
HE'S VERY NICE, ISN'T HE?

276
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:45,163
AH, I KNOW SOME OF YOU
HAVE TO GET HOME RATHER SOON.

277
00:32:45,163 --> 00:32:48,166
SO THERE'S YOUR LITTLE
PRESENT, MY DEAR. THERE.

278
00:32:48,166 --> 00:32:51,169
THANK YOU,
MR. GRIMSDYKE.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

279
00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:55,673
NOW SHALL I TELL YOU
SOMETHING? MY WIFE'S NAME
WAS HELEN. MARY HELEN GRIMSDYKE.

280
00:32:55,673 --> 00:32:59,177
I ALWAYS CALLED HER HELEN.
IT'S A NICE NAME,
ISN'T IT? YEAH.

281
00:32:59,177 --> 00:33:01,179
BYE-BYE THEN.
COME ON, MARK.
 COME ON, JULIE.

282
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:03,982
COME AND SIT HERE.
BYE-BYE, MARK.
BYE-BYE, JULIE.

283
00:33:03,982 --> 00:33:07,819
[ Barking ]
BYE.

284
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,655
BYE.

285
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:13,524
TWO LITTLE DICKEY BIRDS
SITTING ON A WALL.

286
00:33:13,524 --> 00:33:15,526
ONE NAMED PETER.
 ONE NAMED PAUL.

287
00:33:16,027 --> 00:33:18,029
FLY AWAY, PETER.
 FLY AWAY, PAUL.

288
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:20,031
COME BACK, PETER.
 COME BACK, PAUL.

289
00:33:20,031 --> 00:33:22,333
THAT'S IT.
[ Laughs ]
YOU THINK YOU COULD DO THAT?

290
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:26,087
[ Chattering ]

291
00:33:31,292 --> 00:33:33,294
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

292
00:33:33,294 --> 00:33:35,296
GRIMSDYKE, OF COURSE.

293
00:33:35,797 --> 00:33:37,799
HIS USUAL SHELL OUT
TO THE KIDS.

294
00:33:37,799 --> 00:33:40,301
HE DOES IT EVERY YEAR
ON HIS BIRTHDAY.

295
00:33:40,301 --> 00:33:42,804
I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU STAND IT.
STAND WHAT?

296
00:33:42,804 --> 00:33:45,306
LIVING ACROSS THE ROAD
FROM THAT MAN.

297
00:33:45,306 --> 00:33:48,309
HE'S A RUBBISH COLLECTOR.
A DUSTMAN.

298
00:33:48,309 --> 00:33:50,812
HIS PLACE IS AN EYESORE.

299
00:33:50,812 --> 00:33:56,317
THE TOYS HE GIVE THOSE KIDS
HE FINDS IN THE RUBBISH HEAP
AND REPAIRS.

300
00:33:56,317 --> 00:33:58,820
WHY DOESN'T HE SELL OUT?
I'VE MADE HIM OFFERS.

301
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:02,323
HE'S-- HE'S SENTIMENTAL
ABOUT THAT OLD DUMP.

302
00:34:02,824 --> 00:34:05,827
SAYS HE AND HIS WIFE
LIVED THERE FOR THEIR
WHOLE MARRIED LIFE.

303
00:34:05,827 --> 00:34:08,329
AND NOW HE WANTS
TO DIE THERE,
JUST AS SHE DID.

304
00:34:08,830 --> 00:34:11,833
WELL, IT RUINS THE NEIGHBORHOOD
AND DEPRECIATES THE VALUE
OF OUR PROPERTY.

305
00:34:12,333 --> 00:34:14,335
THE INSIDE MUST BE
LIKE A PIGSTY.

306
00:34:14,836 --> 00:34:16,337
HE OWNS THE PLACE
FREE AND CLEAR.

307
00:34:17,839 --> 00:34:19,674
NOTHING WE CAN DO ABOUT IT.

308
00:34:19,674 --> 00:34:23,594
BYE-BYE. SEE YOU TOMORROW.
SHUT THE GATE.
[ Barking ]

309
00:34:23,594 --> 00:34:25,596
BYE-BYE.

310
00:34:40,445 --> 00:34:42,447
ISN'T THERE?

311
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:14,612
[ Footsteps In Distance ]

312
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,377
WHAT ON EARTH
HAVE YOU BEEN DOING?

313
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:33,297
SOMEBODY'S JUST MADE
AN AWFUL MESS OF
MR. BAKER'S GARDEN.

314
00:35:33,798 --> 00:35:39,086
POOR GRIMSDYKE'S NEIGHBOR.
HE WAS SO PROUD
OF HIS PRIZE ROSES.

315
00:35:39,086 --> 00:35:41,589
[ Man ]
MY PRIZE ROSES.

316
00:35:41,589 --> 00:35:44,091
YEARS OF HARD WORK.

317
00:35:44,091 --> 00:35:46,978
IT'S GRIMSDYKE'S DOGS
FOR SURE.

318
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:50,314
THIS IS TOO MUCH.
I'D LIKE TO MAKE
AN OFFICIAL COMPLAINT.

319
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:52,650
[ Whimpers ]
BUT YOU MUSTN'T
TAKE THEM AWAY.

320
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:57,155
THEY'RE MY FRIENDS.
SERGEANT, PLEASE.

321
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,657
IT'S A COURT ORDER,
AND THEY DON'T HAVE LICENSES.

322
00:35:59,657 --> 00:36:02,160
I COULDN'T AFFORD LICENSES.
I'M SORRY, MR. GRIMSDYKE.

323
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:04,662
SERGEANT, PLEASE.

324
00:36:04,662 --> 00:36:06,664
[ Dogs Whimpering ]
[ Door Closing ]

325
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:09,667
[ Van Departs ]

326
00:36:15,706 --> 00:36:19,710
DARLING. DARLING?

327
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:21,712
ARE YOU THERE, DARLING?

328
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:25,716
ARE YOU THERE, DARLING?

329
00:36:28,219 --> 00:36:30,221
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

330
00:36:31,105 --> 00:36:34,058
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

331
00:36:35,059 --> 00:36:38,563
IS THERE ANY-- ANYTHING
YOU WISH TO TELL ME?

332
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:51,042
AH!
[ Shudders ]

333
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:52,877
GIVE ME THE MESSAGE.

334
00:37:17,935 --> 00:37:20,821
D-- D--

335
00:37:20,821 --> 00:37:22,607
WAIT.

336
00:37:32,667 --> 00:37:35,169
DANGER. DANGER?

337
00:37:37,538 --> 00:37:40,591
WHO TO? WHO TO?

338
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:43,511
IS IT ONE
OF THE CHILDREN?

339
00:37:43,511 --> 00:37:46,347
WHO TO?

340
00:37:46,347 --> 00:37:49,800
JUST THINK IT OVER,
COUNCILLOR RAMSEY.

341
00:37:52,803 --> 00:37:55,306
GRIMSDYKE'S DUE
TO RETIRE IN TWO YEARS.

342
00:37:55,306 --> 00:37:58,309
HE'S DONE HIS JOB WELL.
THERE'S NO REASON WHY
THE TOWN COUNCIL--

343
00:37:58,809 --> 00:38:01,812
HE'S TOO OLD.
DON'T YOU THINK
A YOUNGER MAN--

344
00:38:01,812 --> 00:38:03,814
HE'D LOSE
HIS RETIREMENT PAY.

345
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:06,317
AND SAVE THE TOWN
SOME MONEY.

346
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:33,844
POOR OLD GRIMSDYKE.

347
00:38:33,844 --> 00:38:35,680
I DO BELIEVE
HE'S OUT OF A JOB.

348
00:38:52,446 --> 00:38:54,448
HMM.

349
00:38:58,953 --> 00:39:01,956
FLOWERS ARE A LITTLE WILTED,
AREN'T THEY, MY DEAR?

350
00:39:01,956 --> 00:39:03,958
GOD BLESS YOU.

351
00:39:03,958 --> 00:39:07,461
PLENTY MORE IN THE GARDEN.
I'LL GET YOU SOME TOMORROW.

352
00:39:09,463 --> 00:39:12,466
[ Dog Barking ]

353
00:39:19,473 --> 00:39:21,475
OH!

354
00:39:24,979 --> 00:39:26,981
[ Chuckling ]
[ Barking ]

355
00:39:26,981 --> 00:39:29,900
JAMIE! JAMIE!
MY LITTLE JAMIE.

356
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:32,403
OH, I WONDERED
WHERE YOU WERE.

357
00:39:32,903 --> 00:39:35,906
OH, I'M SO GLAD
THEY DIDN'T GET YOU.

358
00:39:35,906 --> 00:39:39,910
WELCOME HOME. OH.
BETTER SAVE MONEY NOW,
HADN'T WE?

359
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:43,581
HEY, LOOK. HELEN,
LOOK WHO'S COME BACK.
OUR LITTLE JAMIE.

360
00:39:44,081 --> 00:39:48,586
AH, THAT'S WONDERFUL.
YOU'RE OUR ONLY FRIEND NOW.
YOU AND THE CHILDREN.

361
00:39:48,586 --> 00:39:52,056
WE THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE
NEIGHBORLY TO LET YOU KNOW
WHAT WAS GOING ON.

362
00:39:52,056 --> 00:39:55,059
IT'S VERY KIND OF YOU
TO DRAW OUR ATTENTION
TO THIS, MR. ELLIOT.

363
00:39:55,059 --> 00:39:58,562
IT'S SO DIFFICULT TO KNOW
WHAT ONE'S CHILDREN GET UP TO
WHEN THEY'RE OUT OF ONE'S SIGHT.

364
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:00,564
AFTER ALL, LAST YEAR
I REMEMBER--

365
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:04,568
YOU CAN TELL FROM
LOOKING AT HIS HOUSE WHAT
A FILTHY OLD MAN HE IS.

366
00:40:04,568 --> 00:40:07,071
CONSTANTLY FILLING IT
WITH CHILDREN.

367
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:09,573
HEAVEN KNOWS WHAT
HIS MOTIVATIONS ARE.

368
00:40:11,525 --> 00:40:14,528
NOW DON'T FORGET WHAT I SAID.
JUST STAY AWAY FROM HIM.

369
00:40:14,528 --> 00:40:16,530
BUT, MUMMY, HE'S SUCH
A NICE OLD MAN.

370
00:40:16,530 --> 00:40:19,834
DON'T ARGUE WITH ME.
YOU'RE NOT TO SEE HIM
AGAIN EVER.

371
00:40:19,834 --> 00:40:22,253
WHY DON'T YOU GO AND PLAY
IN OUR GARDEN?

372
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:24,755
AND DON'T TAKE
ANY MORE SWEETS FROM HIM.

373
00:40:24,755 --> 00:40:28,542
CARRYING RUBBISH ALL DAY.
HIS HOUSE MUST BE FILTHY.

374
00:40:28,542 --> 00:40:32,296
YOU AND YOUR MR. GRIMSDYKE.
NOW, REMEMBER, I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GO ANYWHERE NEAR HIM.

375
00:40:32,296 --> 00:40:34,014
OH, MUM--
AND THAT'S FINAL.

376
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:41,439
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.

377
00:40:41,439 --> 00:40:44,442
EVERYONE WAS SO KIND.
[ Sniffles ]

378
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,945
NOW THIS. NO WORK.

379
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:50,448
NO CHILDREN.

380
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,450
NO ONE TO MAKE TOYS FOR.

381
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:56,954
WELL, NEVER MIND.

382
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:01,959
WE'VE ALWAYS GOT EACH OTHER,
HAVEN'T WE, MY DEAR?

383
00:41:01,959 --> 00:41:04,462
MMM. THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

384
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:09,967
JUST ONE MORE TURN
OF THE SCREW...

385
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:12,720
AND HE'LL SELL HIS PROPERTY
FOR NEXT TO NOTHING.

386
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,889
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

387
00:41:17,391 --> 00:41:19,226
VALENTINE'S DAY.

388
00:41:19,226 --> 00:41:22,646
IT'S JUST TWO WEEKS AWAY.
SO?

389
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:28,152
WE'LL SEND HIM VALENTINES...

390
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:30,905
FROM EVERYONE IN TOWN.

391
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:34,191
OH.
LOTS OF MAIL FOR YOU
TODAY, MR. GRIMSDYKE.

392
00:41:34,191 --> 00:41:37,194
GOOD MORNING.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

393
00:41:37,194 --> 00:41:40,414
WELL, HOW VERY KIND.

394
00:41:41,699 --> 00:41:43,701
MY DEAR, LOOK.

395
00:41:43,701 --> 00:41:46,203
IT'S NOT EVEN CHRISTMAS,
IS IT?

396
00:41:46,203 --> 00:41:49,206
NOT THAT IT MAKES ANY DIFFERENCE
IF IT IS OR NOT.

397
00:41:49,206 --> 00:41:52,009
WHO COULD BE WRITING TO US?
LET'S SEE HERE.

398
00:41:53,460 --> 00:41:56,630
OH! IT'S A VALENTINE CARD.

399
00:41:56,630 --> 00:42:00,634
BUT YOU'RE MY ONLY SWEETHEART.
WHO CAN THIS BE?

400
00:42:00,634 --> 00:42:03,137
"NOISY ARE CHILDREN,
 LOUD IS A BELL,

401
00:42:03,137 --> 00:42:06,640
PUNGENT IS PERFUME,
BUT YOU ONLY SMELL."

402
00:42:07,141 --> 00:42:10,144
HMM?
"NOISY ARE CHILDREN,
 LOUD IS A BELL,

403
00:42:10,144 --> 00:42:13,147
PUNGENT IS PERFUME,
BUT YOU ONLY SMELL."

404
00:42:13,147 --> 00:42:15,950
WHY, I DON'T THINK
I LIKE THAT.

405
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:18,319
LET'S SEE WHAT
WE HAVE HERE.

406
00:42:23,324 --> 00:42:26,961
"A TREE IS BEAUTIFUL
 IF ITS OWNER PRUNES IT,

407
00:42:26,961 --> 00:42:28,963
"BUT OUR TOWN ISN'T...

408
00:42:28,963 --> 00:42:32,466
'CAUSE YOUR PRESENCE
RUINS IT."

409
00:42:34,468 --> 00:42:36,470
OH.

410
00:42:39,473 --> 00:42:41,976
[ Opening Envelope ]

411
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:47,982
"SOME PEOPLE LIVE
 IN THE COUNTRY.

412
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:51,485
"SOME PEOPLE LIVE
 IN THE TOWN.

413
00:42:51,485 --> 00:42:54,488
"WHY DON'T YOU DO
 US A SERVICE?

414
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:59,243
JUMP IN THE RIVER AND--"

415
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:19,630
[ Dog Howling ]

416
00:43:22,883 --> 00:43:24,935
[ Howling Continues ]

417
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:28,105
WHAT'S GRIMSDYKE BEEN
DOING TO THAT MONGREL?

418
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:31,475
HE HASN'T STOPPED
WHINING FOR A WEEK.

419
00:43:33,978 --> 00:43:35,980
YOU KNOW,
COME TO THINK OF IT,

420
00:43:35,980 --> 00:43:38,482
I HAVEN'T SEEN GRIMSDYKE
FOR DAYS.

421
00:43:40,985 --> 00:43:43,320
NOT SINCE VALENTINE'S DAY.

422
00:43:49,243 --> 00:43:51,745
HE CAN'T BE FAR AWAY
IF THE DOOR'S OPEN.

423
00:43:53,747 --> 00:43:55,749
THIS PLACE IS SPOTLESS.

424
00:43:55,749 --> 00:43:57,751
I THOUGHT IT'D BE FILTHY.

425
00:44:13,684 --> 00:44:18,072
[ Creaking ]

426
00:44:35,205 --> 00:44:38,342
[ Man ] "BUT THE MERCIFUL
GOODNESS OF THE LORD
ENDURETH FOREVER AND EVER...

427
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:40,344
[ Whining ]
"UPON THEM THAT FEAR HIM,

428
00:44:40,344 --> 00:44:42,846
"AND HIS RIGHTEOUSNESS
 UPON HIS CHILDREN'S CHILDREN.

429
00:44:42,846 --> 00:44:46,850
"FOR AS MUCH AS IT HATH
 PLEASED ALMIGHTY GOD
 OF HIS GREAT MERCY...

430
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:49,303
TO TAKE UNTO HIMSELF
THE SOUL OF OUR DEAR BROTHER"--

431
00:44:49,803 --> 00:44:54,441
ARTHUR EDWARD GRIMSDYKE.
"HERE DEPARTED.

432
00:44:54,441 --> 00:44:57,444
"WE THEREFORE COMMIT
 HIS BODY TO THE GROUND.

433
00:44:57,444 --> 00:45:00,948
"EARTH TO EARTH,
 ASHES TO ASHES,
[ Dirt Falling On Coffin ]

434
00:45:00,948 --> 00:45:02,950
"DUST TO DUST.

435
00:45:02,950 --> 00:45:05,953
"IN SURE AND CERTAIN HOPE
 OF THE RESURRECTION
 TO ETERNAL LIFE,

436
00:45:05,953 --> 00:45:08,956
THROUGH OUR LORD
JESUS CHRIST"--

437
00:45:08,956 --> 00:45:11,458
IT WAS KIND OF YOU
TO PAY FOR THE BURIAL.

438
00:45:11,458 --> 00:45:13,961
IT WAS THE LEAST I COULD DO.

439
00:45:13,961 --> 00:45:15,963
HE WAS A NEIGHBOR.

440
00:45:58,789 --> 00:46:01,291
WHAT'S THAT?

441
00:46:01,291 --> 00:46:03,293
VALENTINE'S CARDS.

442
00:46:03,293 --> 00:46:07,798
THE ONES LEFT OVER
FROM LAST YEAR WHEN--

443
00:46:08,298 --> 00:46:11,802
MUST BE A YEAR AGO.
TODAY.

444
00:46:12,302 --> 00:46:16,306
IT'S VALENTINE'S DAY.
FEBRUARY THE 14th.

445
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:18,809
A YEAR AGO EXACTLY.

446
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:39,022
[ Sighs ]

447
00:47:41,024 --> 00:47:43,026
I'M GOING TO BED.
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

448
00:47:46,813 --> 00:47:48,565
NIGHT.

449
00:47:48,565 --> 00:47:50,901
NIGHT.

450
00:48:40,284 --> 00:48:42,369
[ Screaming ]

451
00:49:21,742 --> 00:49:23,744
"YOU WERE MEAN...

452
00:49:24,244 --> 00:49:26,546
"AND CRUEL...

453
00:49:26,546 --> 00:49:30,334
"RIGHT FROM THE START.

454
00:49:30,334 --> 00:49:34,338
"NOW YOU REALLY HAVE...

455
00:49:34,338 --> 00:49:36,340
NO"--

456
00:49:38,842 --> 00:49:40,644
[ Screams ]

457
00:49:55,659 --> 00:49:57,911
IT'S TRUE.

458
00:49:57,911 --> 00:50:00,914
IT'S TRUE.

459
00:50:00,914 --> 00:50:03,283
I DIDN'T--

460
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:08,005
DON'TLIKE GRIMSDYKE.

461
00:50:18,382 --> 00:50:20,851
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

462
00:50:23,553 --> 00:50:26,390
[ Monk ]
YOU'LL SEE.

463
00:50:39,319 --> 00:50:41,321
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

464
00:50:42,322 --> 00:50:44,825
WELL, THAT'S IT,
RALPH, I'M AFRAID.

465
00:50:44,825 --> 00:50:46,710
IT'S ALL GONE.

466
00:50:46,710 --> 00:50:51,665
EVERYTHING?
MORETHAN EVERYTHING.
 YOU HAVE DEBTS.

467
00:50:51,665 --> 00:50:56,169
I DID WARN YOU, DIDN'T I,
NOT TO USE THE MONEY THAT
HAD BEEN ENTRUSTED TO YOU?

468
00:50:56,169 --> 00:50:59,089
- THE RISKS
  WERE FAR TOO GREAT.
- THE RISKS?

469
00:50:59,089 --> 00:51:01,591
THE GAINS COULD'VE
BEEN ENORMOUS.

470
00:51:03,093 --> 00:51:05,095
[ Sighs ]

471
00:51:05,095 --> 00:51:07,230
WHAT DO I DO NOW?

472
00:51:08,231 --> 00:51:11,234
WELL, YOU HAVE TWO CHOICES.

473
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:13,103
FIRST, BANKRUPTCY.

474
00:51:13,103 --> 00:51:15,939
AND ACCORDING TO YOU,
THAT WOULD BE DISHONORABLE,
WOULDN'T IT?

475
00:51:15,939 --> 00:51:18,408
OH, COME ON.
LET'S FACE IT.

476
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:21,745
YOU'VE DONE DISHONORABLE THINGS
IN YOUR LIFE BEFORE,
IN YOUR BUSINESS LIFE.

477
00:51:21,745 --> 00:51:25,699
HARD, RUTHLESS--
OH, PERHAPS EVEN CRUEL.

478
00:51:25,699 --> 00:51:28,919
YES, TO BUILD UP
THE JASON EMPIRE,
SOMETIMES I HAD TO BE.

479
00:51:28,919 --> 00:51:31,955
- NO ONE HAS TO BE.
- I DID.

480
00:51:31,955 --> 00:51:36,460
OH, IT'S EASY TO TALK,
BUT I HAD TO FIGHT MY WAY UP
THE HARD WAY.

481
00:51:36,460 --> 00:51:38,712
IF PEOPLE GOT HURT,
THEY GOT HURT.

482
00:51:38,712 --> 00:51:42,132
BUT I ALWAYS PAID MY DEBTS.

483
00:51:42,132 --> 00:51:44,134
NO, I'M NOT GOING
INTO BANKRUPTCY.

484
00:51:44,134 --> 00:51:47,220
WELL, IF YOU INTEND TO TRY
AND PAY OFF YOUR DEBTS,

485
00:51:47,220 --> 00:51:50,607
YOU'LL HAVE TO START
SELLING THINGS,
THINGS OF VALUE--

486
00:51:50,607 --> 00:51:53,777
PROPERTIES, YOUR PAINTINGS--
EVERYTHING.

487
00:51:53,777 --> 00:51:58,482
MY HOUSE?
ALL THE BEAUTIFUL THINGS
I'VE ACQUIRED DURING THE YEARS?

488
00:51:58,482 --> 00:52:00,867
IT'S THE ONLY WAY.

489
00:52:00,867 --> 00:52:03,370
I WON'T DO IT.

490
00:52:04,371 --> 00:52:06,373
I'M AFRAID YOU'LL HAVE TO.

491
00:52:09,126 --> 00:52:11,161
SO, THERE'S
NOTHING ELSE FOR IT.

492
00:52:11,161 --> 00:52:13,163
WE HAVE TO SELL.

493
00:52:13,663 --> 00:52:16,166
OH, I KNOW IT'S A BLOW.

494
00:52:16,166 --> 00:52:20,670
OUR WHOLE LIFE'S IN THEM.
EVERYTHING WE'VE COLLECTED
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

495
00:52:23,256 --> 00:52:25,559
I REMEMBER THAT ONE.

496
00:52:25,559 --> 00:52:28,562
WE GOT IT IN THAT STRANGE
SHOP IN HONG KONG...

497
00:52:28,562 --> 00:52:32,065
WHEN YOU WERE
SELLING GUNS TO--

498
00:52:32,566 --> 00:52:36,570
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT
THE LITTLE MAN IN THE SHOP SAID
TO US WHEN HE SOLD IT TO US?

499
00:52:36,570 --> 00:52:40,574
YES. "USE IT"--
"USE IT WISELY."

500
00:52:40,574 --> 00:52:44,077
HMM! I WONDER WHAT
HE MEANT BY THAT.

501
00:52:44,077 --> 00:52:47,080
RALPH, HAVE YOU--

502
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:51,084
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THIS WRITING
THAT'S INSCRIBED ON THE BOTTOM
OF THIS STATUETTE?

503
00:52:51,084 --> 00:52:54,588
WRITING?
HMM, YES,
HERE AT THE BASE.

504
00:52:56,957 --> 00:53:02,212
"THREE WISHES I GIVE
 AND NO MORE...

505
00:53:02,212 --> 00:53:07,050
"TO EACH OWNER OF ME...

506
00:53:07,050 --> 00:53:09,052
"SO KEEP SCORE.

507
00:53:10,053 --> 00:53:14,057
"EACH WISH WILL COME TRUE...

508
00:53:14,057 --> 00:53:18,195
SO TAKE CARE WHAT YOU DO."

509
00:53:19,529 --> 00:53:22,282
I CAN'T READ THE REST,
BUT THE LAST WORD IS...

510
00:53:22,282 --> 00:53:25,569
"DEPLORE."
WHAT DOES IT ALL MEAN?

511
00:53:25,569 --> 00:53:27,571
"USE IT WISELY."

512
00:53:29,072 --> 00:53:31,575
IF ONLY IT COULD GIVE US
THREE WISHES.

513
00:53:31,575 --> 00:53:33,577
THAT'S STORYBOOK NONSENSE.

514
00:53:33,577 --> 00:53:37,497
- BUT IT REMINDS ME OF A TALE
  I ONCE READ. WHAT WAS IT?
-WE COULD PAY ALL OUR DEBTS.

515
00:53:37,497 --> 00:53:40,300
"THE MONKEY'S PAW."
THAT'S WHAT IT WAS.
I WISH--

516
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:42,302
I READ IT WHEN
 I WAS AT SCHOOL.

517
00:53:42,302 --> 00:53:44,804
I WISH FOR LOTS
AND LOTS OF MONEY.

518
00:53:44,804 --> 00:53:48,808
OH, NO, NO!
TOO LATE.
I ALREADY HAVE.

519
00:53:48,808 --> 00:53:51,311
AND I'VE JUST
REMEMBERED WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE END OF THE STORY.

520
00:53:51,311 --> 00:53:54,814
WHY, YOU SAID YOURSELF,
IT WAS JUST A STORY--

521
00:53:54,814 --> 00:53:58,818
LIKE OUR THREE WISHES.
[ Phone Ringing ]

522
00:54:02,939 --> 00:54:05,242
HELLO? OH, HELLO, CHARLES.

523
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:08,111
I'D LIKE YOU TO
COME DOWN TO MY OFFICE.
WHAT, RIGHT NOW?

524
00:54:08,111 --> 00:54:10,113
YES, STRAIGHTAWAY.
WHAT'S IT ALL ABOUT?

525
00:54:10,113 --> 00:54:12,782
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT.
 IT'S ABOUT MONEY.

526
00:54:12,782 --> 00:54:15,285
I'D LIKE YOU
TO COME STRAIGHTAWAY.

527
00:54:15,285 --> 00:54:17,454
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

528
00:54:20,957 --> 00:54:23,960
THAT'S CHARLES.
HE WANTS ME TO GO
AND SEE HIM RIGHT AWAY.

529
00:54:23,960 --> 00:54:26,963
HE SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT MONEY.
MONEY?

530
00:54:33,470 --> 00:54:35,972
[ Birds Chirping ]

531
00:54:42,112 --> 00:54:45,448
MAYBE OUR WISH WILL
COME TRUE AFTER ALL.
[ Car Engine Starting ]

532
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:26,966
[ Rings ]

533
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:29,469
HELLO?
[ Man On Phone ]
IS THAT MR. GREGORY?

534
00:56:29,469 --> 00:56:32,472
YES, YES, SPEAKING.
I'M SORRY TO TELL YOU, SIR,
BUT YOUR CLIENT, RALPH JASON,

535
00:56:32,472 --> 00:56:34,474
HAS BEEN KILLED
IN A CAR CRASH.

536
00:56:34,474 --> 00:56:38,978
IN HIS CAR?
YES, ON THE ROAD
ABOUT 10 MILES FROM HIS HOME.

537
00:56:38,978 --> 00:56:41,848
WELL, UH, HAVE YOU TOLD ENID--
MRS. JASON YET?

538
00:56:41,848 --> 00:56:44,317
NO, NOT YET.

539
00:56:44,317 --> 00:56:46,820
WE FOUND SOME LETTERS
FROM YOU IN HIS POCKET.

540
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:50,323
THEY INDICATE THAT YOU'RE
NOT ONLY HIS SOLICITOR BUT
A CLOSE FRIEND OF THE FAMILY.

541
00:56:50,323 --> 00:56:52,742
WE THOUGHT IT BETTER
THAT YOU BREAK THE NEWS.

542
00:56:52,742 --> 00:56:56,246
YES, YES.
 YES, OF COURSE.

543
00:56:56,246 --> 00:56:58,248
LEAVE IT TO ME.

544
00:56:58,248 --> 00:57:00,750
I'LL TELL HER.
THANK YOU, SIR.

545
00:57:07,957 --> 00:57:10,960
RALPH? DEAD?

546
00:57:15,465 --> 00:57:17,967
THEY FOUND HIM IN
THE WRECKAGE OF HIS CAR.

547
00:57:17,967 --> 00:57:20,470
HE'D OBVIOUSLY
LOST CONTROL,
SKIDDED.

548
00:57:20,470 --> 00:57:22,972
[ Sobbing ]

549
00:57:22,972 --> 00:57:26,976
ENID, THIS MAY NOT BE
THE BEST MOMENT TO TALK
ABOUT THIS, BUT, UH,

550
00:57:26,976 --> 00:57:29,979
IT MAY ALLEVIATE
SOME OF YOUR OTHER WORRIES.

551
00:57:29,979 --> 00:57:32,982
YOU REALIZE THIS ACCIDENT
MAKES YOU A RICH WOMAN.

552
00:57:35,485 --> 00:57:37,987
RICH?

553
00:57:37,987 --> 00:57:40,990
RALPH'S INSURANCE.
HE ALWAYS CARRIED
A LARGE POLICY,

554
00:57:40,990 --> 00:57:44,494
WITH A DOUBLE INDEMNITY
AGAINST ACCIDENT.

555
00:57:44,494 --> 00:57:49,999
OH, CHARLES, I WISHED
FOR LOTS AND LOTS OF MONEY.
RALPH WARNED ME NOT TO.

556
00:57:49,999 --> 00:57:53,002
NO, THAT'S A COINCIDENCE,
SURELY.
NO, IT'S NO COINCIDENCE.

557
00:57:53,503 --> 00:57:55,505
THAT STATUETTE--

558
00:57:56,506 --> 00:57:59,008
IT GAVE US THREE WISHES.

559
00:57:59,509 --> 00:58:03,012
I USED ONE OF THEM TO WISH
FOR LOTS AND LOTS OF MONEY.

560
00:58:04,013 --> 00:58:06,316
NOW I'M GOING TO WISH
FOR RALPH BACK.

561
00:58:10,603 --> 00:58:12,605
CHARLES.

562
00:58:12,605 --> 00:58:15,575
DO YOU KNOW THE STORY
OF "THE MONKEY'S PAW"?

563
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:19,078
THAT'S THE STORY OF
THE OLD COUPLE WHO ARE
GIVEN A MONKEY'S PAW...

564
00:58:19,078 --> 00:58:21,581
WHICH ENTITLES THEM
TO THREE WISHES.

565
00:58:21,581 --> 00:58:25,535
THEY WISH FOR MONEY,
AND THEY GET THE MONEY...

566
00:58:25,535 --> 00:58:28,421
BECAUSE THEIR SON
IS KILLED...

567
00:58:28,421 --> 00:58:30,423
IN A MACHINE IN HIS FACTORY,
CRUSHED.

568
00:58:30,423 --> 00:58:35,178
ENID. YOU MUSTN'T
WISH RALPH BACK.
WHY NOT?

569
00:58:35,178 --> 00:58:38,965
WELL, IN THE STORY,
THIS MOTHER WISHES HER SON BACK,
AND HE DOES COME BACK,

570
00:58:38,965 --> 00:58:43,269
BUT IN THE CONDITION
IN WHICH HE DIED--
MUTILATED, MANGLED, TORN.

571
00:58:43,269 --> 00:58:46,523
[ Enid ]
I MUST BE CAREFUL
NOT TO MAKE THE SAME MISTAKE.

572
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:52,362
I SHALL WISH
THAT RALPH WERE BACK
AS HE WAS BEFORE THE ACCIDENT.

573
00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:57,367
I WISH...

574
00:58:57,367 --> 00:59:00,370
RALPH WERE BACK
EXACTLY AS HE WAS...

575
00:59:00,370 --> 00:59:03,373
IMMEDIATELY BEFORE
THE ACCIDENT.

576
00:59:05,375 --> 00:59:08,378
[ Pounding ]

577
00:59:12,715 --> 00:59:15,385
[ Pounding ]

578
00:59:42,445 --> 00:59:45,448
OPEN IT! QUICKLY!
NO, NO. DON'T LOOK.

579
00:59:45,448 --> 00:59:47,450
HIS BODY WAS MANGLED
IN THE CRASH.

580
00:59:48,952 --> 00:59:50,703
MANGLED?
IT WASN'T MANGLED.

581
00:59:50,703 --> 00:59:55,258
MR. JASON DIED OF A HEART ATTACK
AT THE WHEEL.

582
00:59:56,259 --> 00:59:59,262
[ Door Closes ]

583
00:59:59,262 --> 01:00:03,266
I WISHED TO BRING HIM BACK
AS HE WAS IMMEDIATELY BEFORE
THE ACCIDENT.

584
01:00:03,766 --> 01:00:08,271
BUT HE WAS ALREADY DEAD--
DEAD FROM A HEART ATTACK.
SO THE ACCIDENT DIDN'T KILL HIM.

585
01:00:16,613 --> 01:00:19,616
ONLY ONE MORE WISH.
ENID--

586
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:21,618
PLEASE GO AWAY.
LEAVE ME ALONE.
PLEASE--

587
01:00:21,618 --> 01:00:24,120
I WANT TO BE ALONE
WITH HIM, PLEASE.

588
01:00:42,722 --> 01:00:45,642
ONLY ONE MORE WISH.

589
01:00:45,642 --> 01:00:47,644
ONLY ONE.

590
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:50,647
I MUSTN'T WASTE IT.
 I MUST BE CAREFUL.

591
01:00:58,571 --> 01:01:01,574
OH, PLEASE, PLEASE,

592
01:01:01,574 --> 01:01:05,078
I WISH RALPH
WERE ALIVE NOW.

593
01:01:05,078 --> 01:01:07,580
I DON'T WANT HIM
TO DIE EVER.

594
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:11,084
I WANT HIM MOVING,
BREATHING, TALKING, ALIVE--

595
01:01:11,084 --> 01:01:13,586
NOW, FOREVER!

596
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:15,755
[ Screaming ]

597
01:01:15,755 --> 01:01:17,457
RALPH!
OH, ENID!

598
01:01:18,925 --> 01:01:20,677
RALPH! CHARLES!

599
01:01:20,677 --> 01:01:22,628
HELP ME!
WHAT'S HAPPENED?

600
01:01:22,628 --> 01:01:24,714
- OH!
- [ Charles ]
  WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?

601
01:01:24,714 --> 01:01:27,850
I WISHED ALIVE AGAIN-- FOREVER!

602
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:31,471
DON'T YOU REALIZE HE'S
BEEN EMBALMED? HIS VEINS ARE
FILLED WITH EMBALMING FLUID...

603
01:01:31,471 --> 01:01:33,306
BURNING INTO HIM!
OH, NO!

604
01:01:33,773 --> 01:01:35,058
[ Sobbing ]

605
01:01:36,726 --> 01:01:39,028
ENID! DO SOMETHING!

606
01:01:39,028 --> 01:01:41,864
[ Screaming Continues ]

607
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:46,986
FOR GOD'S SAKE, ENID!
HELP ME!

608
01:01:49,706 --> 01:01:52,408
NO, NO! ENID, DON'T!

609
01:01:52,408 --> 01:01:54,794
- AAH! AAH!
- [ Enid Grunting ]

610
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:23,740
BUT DON'T YOU SEE?
YOU WISHED HIM ALIVE FOREVER!

611
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:27,660
YOU CAN'T KILL HIM!
EVERY PIECE OF HIM
IS ALIVE STILL!

612
01:02:30,029 --> 01:02:32,749
ALIVE AND-- AND SUFFERING...

613
01:02:32,749 --> 01:02:34,917
FOREVER.

614
01:02:41,791 --> 01:02:43,793
[ Sobbing ]

615
01:02:49,882 --> 01:02:52,218
[ Man ]
WELL, WHAT DID YOU SEE?

616
01:02:59,642 --> 01:03:03,146
WHAT DID HE SEE?
WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT
IS WHAT YOU WILL SEE.

617
01:03:03,146 --> 01:03:05,148
WHO ARE YOU?
WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH US?

618
01:03:05,648 --> 01:03:08,651
TO WARN YOU OF WHAT MAY HAPPEN.
I DON'T CARE ABOUT
YOUR WARNINGS.

619
01:03:08,651 --> 01:03:10,653
I WANT TO GET
OUT OF HERE.
VERY WELL.

620
01:03:10,653 --> 01:03:13,656
BUT YOU SHOULD
HEED THE WARNING.

621
01:03:26,469 --> 01:03:28,471
[ Panting ]

622
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:32,258
[ Birds Chirping ]

623
01:03:36,012 --> 01:03:38,347
[ Parking Brake Cranks ]

624
01:03:43,352 --> 01:03:45,354
MR. ROGERS?
MAJORROGERS.

625
01:03:45,354 --> 01:03:48,741
SHOW ME TO MY QUARTERS
AND HAVE SOMEBODY GET MY KIT IN,
WILL YOU?

626
01:03:48,741 --> 01:03:51,194
SHANE, HERE.
[ Barking ]

627
01:03:51,194 --> 01:03:53,196
GOOD BOY.

628
01:04:05,041 --> 01:04:07,043
[ Clanks ]

629
01:04:19,222 --> 01:04:22,225
THERE WERE PICTURES
ON THE WALL.
WHERE HAVE THEY GONE?

630
01:04:22,225 --> 01:04:24,527
PERSONAL PROPERTY
OF YOUR PREDECESSOR, SIR.

631
01:04:25,811 --> 01:04:28,314
WELL, WE MUST GET SOME MORE.

632
01:04:28,314 --> 01:04:31,317
I'LL GO DOWN TO LONDON,
HAVE A LOOK AROUND
THE GALLERIES.

633
01:04:32,318 --> 01:04:34,820
WHERE ARE THE MEN--
UH, THE PATIENTS?

634
01:04:34,820 --> 01:04:37,540
THEY'VE GONE TO LUNCH, SIR.

635
01:04:37,540 --> 01:04:40,042
YOU MEAN DINNER, DON'T YOU?

636
01:04:40,960 --> 01:04:43,462
BON APPEÉÉTIT,MR. CARTER.

637
01:04:44,463 --> 01:04:46,465
THANK YOU, HARRY.

638
01:04:46,465 --> 01:04:48,467
[ Men Chattering ]

639
01:05:11,991 --> 01:05:13,993
[ Man Coughs ]

640
01:05:22,001 --> 01:05:24,337
GOOD MORNING.

641
01:05:25,838 --> 01:05:28,541
MY NAME IS ROGERS.
MAJOR WILLIAM ROGERS.

642
01:05:28,541 --> 01:05:31,928
I'VE BEEN APPOINTED
YOUR NEW SUPERINTENDENT HERE,
AND TAKE UP MY DUTIES TODAY.

643
01:05:31,928 --> 01:05:36,182
I'VE HAD CONSIDERABLE EXPERIENCE
IN DEALING WITH MEN
AS AN OFFICER IN THE ARMY.

644
01:05:36,182 --> 01:05:39,552
I PROMISE YOU I WILL DO THIS JOB
TO THE BEST OF MY ABILITY.

645
01:05:39,552 --> 01:05:42,054
I HOPE WE'LL ALL
GET ALONG WELL.

646
01:05:42,054 --> 01:05:44,056
IF THERE ARE
ANY COMPLAINTS,

647
01:05:44,056 --> 01:05:47,560
I SHALL BE PLEASED TO DEAL
WITH THEM IN MY OFFICE
AT ANY TIME.

648
01:05:47,560 --> 01:05:50,646
- GOOD MORNING.
- [ All Mumbling ]
  GOOD MORNING.

649
01:05:50,646 --> 01:05:52,732
MORNING.

650
01:05:56,819 --> 01:05:58,955
- SHANE.
-[ Barking ]

651
01:06:01,073 --> 01:06:03,376
[ Door Closes ]

652
01:06:10,800 --> 01:06:12,802
WELL, SHANE,

653
01:06:13,302 --> 01:06:15,304
AFTER I'VE MADE
A FEW CHANGES,

654
01:06:15,304 --> 01:06:17,306
I THINK WE'RE GONNA
LIKE IT HERE.

655
01:06:21,143 --> 01:06:22,979
[ Wind Whistling ]

656
01:06:49,422 --> 01:06:51,424
STONE COLD.

657
01:06:51,424 --> 01:06:54,427
IT'S ALWAYS
LIKE THAT NOW.
[ Coughing ]

658
01:06:54,427 --> 01:06:56,429
[ Wheezing ]

659
01:06:56,429 --> 01:06:58,931
ALL RIGHT, OLD BOY?

660
01:06:58,931 --> 01:07:00,933
ALL RIGHT.

661
01:07:00,933 --> 01:07:03,436
I'LL GET YOU
AN EXTRA BLANKET.

662
01:07:45,311 --> 01:07:47,813
[ Knocking ]
YES?

663
01:08:06,332 --> 01:08:08,667
THE MEN HAVE ASKED ME
TO COME AND TALK TO YOU.

664
01:08:08,667 --> 01:08:10,453
YES?

665
01:08:10,453 --> 01:08:12,838
IT'S ABOUT THE HEATING.

666
01:08:16,092 --> 01:08:20,262
IT'S BEEN VERY COLD
THESE PAST FEW NIGHTS.
WE WONDERED IF YOU--

667
01:08:20,262 --> 01:08:23,883
FOR REASONS OF ECONOMY,
THE HEATING IS NOW TURNED OFF
EACH EVENING AT 2000 HOURS.

668
01:08:26,852 --> 01:08:30,689
YOU SHOULD ALL BE
IN BED BY THEN. AFTER ALL,
THERE'S NO POINT IN STAYING UP.

669
01:08:30,689 --> 01:08:33,943
YOU CAN'T SEE ANYTHING.
THE BEDS ARE COLD.

670
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:36,312
THERE AREN'T
ENOUGH BLANKETS.

671
01:08:36,312 --> 01:08:39,315
I'M TRYING TO RUN
THIS PLACE AS EFFICIENTLY
AND AS ECONOMICALLY AS I CAN.

672
01:08:39,315 --> 01:08:43,119
I'M AFRAID THE CURRENT BUDGET
DOES NOT INCLUDE THE COSTS
OF NEW BLANKETS.

673
01:08:43,119 --> 01:08:45,788
DO YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT BLIND PEOPLE?

674
01:08:45,788 --> 01:08:49,158
NO, I CAN'T SAY I DO,
UNTIL I TOOK OVER THIS JOB.

675
01:08:49,158 --> 01:08:53,462
BUT I WAS IN THE ARMY FOR
OVER 20 YEARS, AND I LEARNED TO
HANDLE ALL KINDS OF MEN THERE.

676
01:08:53,462 --> 01:08:57,666
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT, SIR,
WE ARE NOT SOLDIERS.

677
01:08:57,666 --> 01:09:00,419
AND BLIND PEOPLE ARE NOT
LIKE PEOPLE WITH SIGHT.

678
01:09:01,887 --> 01:09:03,889
WE HAVE LOST ONE SENSE,

679
01:09:03,889 --> 01:09:07,893
BUT THE LOSS OF THAT ONE SENSE
ONLY TENDS TO SHARPEN
THE OTHERS.

680
01:09:09,395 --> 01:09:11,263
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

681
01:09:11,263 --> 01:09:14,066
WE FEEL THINGS MORE ACUTELY.

682
01:09:15,484 --> 01:09:18,487
IF FOOD IS BAD,
IT TASTES WORSE TO US.

683
01:09:18,487 --> 01:09:21,991
IF A ROOM IS DIRTY,
WE FEEL EVERY SPECK.

684
01:09:23,492 --> 01:09:27,329
IF AN INSECT SCURRIES
ACROSS THE FLOOR, WE HEAR IT.

685
01:09:27,329 --> 01:09:31,000
AND IF IT'S COLD,
WE FEEL THE COLD MORE.

686
01:09:32,835 --> 01:09:37,756
WHY DON'T YOU SELL
THAT PAINTING AND BUY US FUEL
OR EXTRA BLANKETS?

687
01:09:37,756 --> 01:09:40,259
I WAS NOT AWARE THAT THE
ADMINISTRATION OF EXPENDITURE
FOR THIS ESTABLISHMENT...

688
01:09:40,259 --> 01:09:42,261
HAD BEEN HANDED OVER TO YOU,
MR. CARTER.

689
01:09:42,261 --> 01:09:44,263
GOOD MORNING.

690
01:09:54,857 --> 01:09:57,059
[ Door Slams ]

691
01:10:04,366 --> 01:10:07,369
DISHWATER.
FILTHY MUCK.

692
01:10:07,870 --> 01:10:09,872
THERE'S NO MEAT IN IT.

693
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:30,392
SORRY, DAD,
THERE AIN'T NO MORE.

694
01:10:30,392 --> 01:10:32,394
NO SECOND HELPING?

695
01:10:32,394 --> 01:10:35,898
WELL, RATIONS WERE CUT,
YOU SEE?

696
01:10:35,898 --> 01:10:39,768
SUPERINTENDENT SAYS HE'S
DOING THE BEST HE CAN
WITH PRICES SO HIGH.

697
01:10:56,035 --> 01:10:59,538
IT'S CUSTOMARY
TO KNOCK ON THE DOOR
OF A PRIVATE OFFICE.

698
01:10:59,538 --> 01:11:02,541
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
CAN'T YOU SEE
I'M HAVING MY LUNCH?

699
01:11:02,541 --> 01:11:07,046
WHAT IS IT?
NICE JUICY STEAK,
WHILE WE GET NOTHING BUT SLOP?

700
01:11:07,046 --> 01:11:10,549
I DO THE BEST I CAN FOR YOU
WITHIN THE LIMITS OF THE BUDGET
PROVIDED FOR ME.

701
01:11:10,549 --> 01:11:15,054
BUT YOU EAT MEAT...
AND DRINK WINE.
I AM THE OFFICER IN CHARGE.

702
01:11:15,054 --> 01:11:18,057
THIS ISN'T THE BLOODY ARMY!
MR. CARTER!

703
01:11:18,557 --> 01:11:21,560
IN THE KINGDOM OF THE BLIND,
EVEN THE ONE-EYED MAN IS KING.

704
01:11:22,444 --> 01:11:24,280
- SHANE!
- [ Barking ]

705
01:11:29,485 --> 01:11:31,320
SHANE, STAY.

706
01:11:39,495 --> 01:11:41,497
HERE.

707
01:11:48,587 --> 01:11:50,389
[ Gasping ]

708
01:11:52,891 --> 01:11:54,893
[ Wheezing ]

709
01:11:54,893 --> 01:11:56,895
[ Coughing ]

710
01:12:18,917 --> 01:12:20,919
DOCTOR.

711
01:12:20,919 --> 01:12:23,422
GET A DOCTOR.

712
01:12:33,766 --> 01:12:36,719
DO YOU REALIZE
IT'S GONE MIDNIGHT?

713
01:12:39,221 --> 01:12:42,224
DOCTOR!
WHO WANTS A DOCTOR?

714
01:12:42,725 --> 01:12:44,226
IT'S GREENWOOD, SIR.

715
01:12:45,728 --> 01:12:47,730
WELL, CAN'T IT WAIT
TILL THE MORNING?

716
01:12:47,730 --> 01:12:51,233
HE'S ILL, SIR. VERY ILL.

717
01:12:52,735 --> 01:12:55,237
WELL, I SUPPOSE
I'D BETTER TAKE A LOOK.

718
01:12:57,706 --> 01:12:59,541
[ Barking ]

719
01:12:59,541 --> 01:13:01,877
SHANE, WAIT.

720
01:13:02,995 --> 01:13:05,631
BLANKET.

721
01:13:19,344 --> 01:13:21,346
[ Wind Whistling ]

722
01:13:24,850 --> 01:13:26,852
WELL, WHICH ONE
IS GREENWOOD?

723
01:13:45,370 --> 01:13:46,872
THE MAN IS DEAD.

724
01:14:09,144 --> 01:14:11,146
VERY WELL.

725
01:17:41,406 --> 01:17:43,659
[ Barking ]

726
01:17:54,036 --> 01:17:55,954
SHANE?

727
01:17:57,956 --> 01:17:59,958
SHANE?

728
01:17:59,958 --> 01:18:01,793
SHANE?

729
01:18:02,294 --> 01:18:05,797
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING? GO BACK
TO YOUR ROOMS, ALL OF YOU!

730
01:18:07,799 --> 01:18:10,802
IT'S OUR TURN TO
GIVE THE ORDERS NOW,

731
01:18:11,303 --> 01:18:14,306
MAJOR ROGERS, SIR.

732
01:18:15,307 --> 01:18:18,310
WELL, WHAT-- WHAT IS IT?
WHAT--

733
01:18:18,310 --> 01:18:20,312
WH-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

734
01:18:25,817 --> 01:18:27,869
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

735
01:18:28,870 --> 01:18:31,373
[ Chattering, Grunting ]

736
01:18:51,226 --> 01:18:53,845
[ Door Slams ]

737
01:18:53,845 --> 01:18:56,181
[ Pounding ]

738
01:18:57,733 --> 01:18:59,735
LET ME OUT OF HERE!

739
01:19:02,070 --> 01:19:04,573
LET ME OUT!

740
01:19:07,075 --> 01:19:09,077
[ Shane Whining ]

741
01:19:14,499 --> 01:19:16,868
SHANE.
[ Barking ]

742
01:19:18,336 --> 01:19:19,755
SHANE.

743
01:19:22,374 --> 01:19:25,377
ALL RIGHT, BOY.
 ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT, BOY.

744
01:19:25,377 --> 01:19:27,796
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO MY DOG?

745
01:19:33,769 --> 01:19:35,771
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO MY DOG?

746
01:19:39,691 --> 01:19:42,194
[ Birds Chirping ]

747
01:19:46,031 --> 01:19:48,950
[ Clattering ]
[ Shane Growling ]

748
01:19:53,455 --> 01:19:55,457
[ Barking ]

749
01:20:44,539 --> 01:20:46,925
[ Barking In Distance ]

750
01:21:19,207 --> 01:21:21,710
[ Grunting ]
LET ME GO!

751
01:21:21,710 --> 01:21:23,712
LET ME GO!

752
01:21:27,999 --> 01:21:30,001
[ Grunts ]
LET ME GO!

753
01:21:30,502 --> 01:21:32,504
LET ME GO!

754
01:21:35,507 --> 01:21:38,143
[ Grunts ]
LET ME GO!

755
01:21:43,932 --> 01:21:46,434
[ Barking Continues ]

756
01:22:02,534 --> 01:22:06,371
YOUR DOG SEEMS
TO BE GETTING HUNGRY,
MAJOR ROGERS.

757
01:22:06,371 --> 01:22:08,590
FEED HIM, PLEASE.
PLEASE, FEED HIM.

758
01:22:08,590 --> 01:22:10,792
ALL IN GOOD TIME.

759
01:22:10,792 --> 01:22:15,096
YES, BUT YOU MUST FEED HIM.
HE-- HE'LL BE DANGEROUS.
HE'LL GO WILD, BERSERK!

760
01:22:16,598 --> 01:22:19,601
I KNOW, MAJOR ROGERS, SIR.

761
01:23:12,487 --> 01:23:14,856
[ Barking Continues ]

762
01:23:14,856 --> 01:23:17,359
[ Clattering Continues ]

763
01:23:36,094 --> 01:23:39,881
WHAT ARE YOU...
DOING OUT THERE?

764
01:23:41,299 --> 01:23:44,803
YOU'LL SEE... SOON ENOUGH.

765
01:24:08,460 --> 01:24:11,463
LOOK, GIVE ME SOMETHING TO EAT,
PLEASE. PLEASE!

766
01:24:11,963 --> 01:24:16,084
I HAVEN'T HAD ANYTHING TO EAT
OR DRINK FOR OVER TWO DAYS.
PLEASE, PLEASE!

767
01:24:23,224 --> 01:24:25,977
WELL, AT LEAST FEED MY DOG,
PLEASE!

768
01:24:25,977 --> 01:24:27,812
HE'LL BE FED, ALL RIGHT,

769
01:24:31,015 --> 01:24:34,018
MAJOR ROGERS, SIR.

770
01:24:45,413 --> 01:24:47,916
[ Wood Scraping ]

771
01:24:48,416 --> 01:24:49,918
[ Creaking ]

772
01:24:55,006 --> 01:24:57,008
[ Shane Snarling
  In Distance ]

773
01:25:36,548 --> 01:25:38,800
[ Creaking ]

774
01:26:19,507 --> 01:26:21,593
[ Screams ]

775
01:27:11,976 --> 01:27:13,394
AAH!

776
01:27:38,753 --> 01:27:40,538
AAH!

777
01:28:00,058 --> 01:28:01,776
YOU--

778
01:28:01,776 --> 01:28:04,112
[ Snarling ]

779
01:28:11,653 --> 01:28:13,788
[ Barking ]

780
01:28:21,546 --> 01:28:25,383
NO! SHANE!
[ Screams ]

781
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:34,642
WHAT IS ALL THIS?

782
01:28:34,642 --> 01:28:37,645
I'M ON MY WAY
TO A NEW JOB.

783
01:28:37,645 --> 01:28:41,149
I DON'T KNOW...
WHY I STOPPED HERE.

784
01:28:41,149 --> 01:28:43,901
I DO.

785
01:28:48,489 --> 01:28:50,358
NOW YOU MAY GO.

786
01:28:52,827 --> 01:28:54,829
[ Scraping ]

787
01:28:55,830 --> 01:28:58,616
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

788
01:29:13,598 --> 01:29:16,684
BUT HOW CAN WE--
WHERE ARE WE?

789
01:29:16,684 --> 01:29:22,523
IN A PLACE WHERE
PEOPLE GO WHO HAVE DIED
WITHOUT REPENTANCE.

790
01:29:22,523 --> 01:29:25,977
YOU SEE,
I WASN'T WARNING YOU,

791
01:29:25,977 --> 01:29:29,480
BUT TELLING YOU WHY
YOU ARE HERE...

792
01:29:29,480 --> 01:29:32,200
FOR ALL ETERNITY.

793
01:29:35,987 --> 01:29:38,122
[ Screams ]

794
01:30:20,581 --> 01:30:23,034
AND NOW...

795
01:30:25,036 --> 01:30:27,038
WHO'S NEXT?

796
01:30:28,539 --> 01:30:31,542
PERHAPS YOU?

797
01:30:31,542 --> 01:30:34,045
[ Thunderclap ]

